    <tr>
      <td valign="bottom"><big><big><font face="Arial" color='White'>R.I.P. of my 'real' interest in EQ</font></big></big></td>
      <td valign="bottom" align="right">
      
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td><font face="Arial" color='White'>by Sladen Declerq
          </font></td>
          <td><p align="right"><font face="Arial" color='White'><small>posted 1/1/00 10:24:47 PM
          </small></font></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><font face="Arial" color='White'><br>Look at the game from *my* persepective.  I now play a level 51 cleric.  Yes, I have no yellow to fill in my bar.  I have a max 218 wis due to the few assorted pieces of purple I don due to much death and aggravation.  I have died 4 times since the bar went full yellow. On none of those select occassions did I lose actual yellow off my bar.  Yes, I have the level 49 ressurrection spell and simply had no reason to ressurect myself.  Sladen is 'finished', etched in gold.  My 'twink' is a level 18 necromancer with 209 int, oracle robe, full quest items, yadda yadda.  He's 'done' with to, just needs to powerlevel.  I play on Veeshan.  There are sooo many high level players the zones like Lower Guk and Sol B are insanely crowded at all times.. You can walk from the Ice Bones to the Lord Room with no invis on and cannot find a frog to kill.  It's that bad.<BR><BR>There is but one guild that can successfully break Hate, or organize Dragon runs quick enough.  I'm not in it.  So all that's left for me is to refine tactics.  Knowing the full power of a 50 cleric and knowing the inherit value of enemy AI, I can solo pull almost anything in Lower guk.  I can solo the Executioner room (Exe Axe, Exe Hood), the Sage room (Runed Cowl, Braided Cinch Cord), the Cavalier room (Dark Reaver, Adamantite Epolets), the Sav room (Black Enamalled BP, Black Enamalled Mace), the Assassain Room (Serrated Bone Dirk, thick Banded Belt, Light Burlap Sack), the Ritualist (Black Embroided Cape/Sleeves).  I can do this with ease, breaking up the spawn on my own if it's full rooms.  The is little challenge left in this game.   If I was a gimp, I could make a killing on Ebay, every day. Instead I choose to equip my guild rather well, and the mid levels love me for it.  So why do I still play?  heh, nothing better to do.  That's life.  But to everyone that cries about 'twinking', they aren't in tune to the game.  'twinking' ended for me eons ago.  I'm at the point where I'm giving stuff away, getting reckless merely because I could care less if I die (altho I never do unless someone intentionally trains me out of a room, which of course happens often on Veeshan -- Even then they die for their efforts more often then not, while I gate to safety or just go invulnerable and skip to the zone).  <BR>     That's the state of EQ now.   If you don't know enough people to tackle Hate, Fear, and Dragons, you now have the option of fighting in Lower Guk and Sol B till you get completely bored and quit EQ.  Verant fixed up Kithicor Forest and Kedge Keep.  Yay.  Kith has no items really to lure most people to it, and is only a zone for mid levels for half the eQ day.  Kedge is a major pain in the tail, and with server overcrowding it's sooooo much fun to see your ranger/druid go LD right before it's time to refresh enduring breath buffs, waveing goodbye to your dead tanks as you gate to safety.  Another fine idea destroyed by reality.  Splitpaw could have been used to allieviate overcrowding, instead it was made another 25-40 place for twinks to powerlevel.  Paineel and the Hole are still rumored to be mid level dungeons, again the fault of Verant for not realizing there are HUNDEREDS of daily players on Veeshan, Fenin Ro, and other servers that are squabbling over the few frogs and kobolds that manage to survive the daily terror they face by the 70-100 players in Lower Guk/Sol B (each zone) each day.<BR><BR>Welp, I'mstill playing the game, the necro is fun to run around, altho Oasis and South Karana is mainly a KS fest between the twinks.  That's just another of the string of problems.  EQ is the best game to come our way in this genre, but it's starting to need a little boost.  The constant 'nerfing' is only making more and more good people leave the game, they need to fix buggy pathign codes and redo some dungeons that never get used, into higher MOB dungeons (Najena?  Splitpaw? something new?  Maybe just Lake Rathe or one of the Karanas?).  Well, I've said my piece.. I'm out<BR><BR>Sladen Declerq<BR>Level 51 Cleric<BR>Veeshan</td>
    </tr>

